01:32:45.340 --> 01:32:47.340
Don't sweat, Denny.

01:32:47.340 --> 01:32:48.340
I know how to plot a course.

01:32:48.340 --> 01:32:50.340
You never trust me.

01:32:50.340 --> 01:32:52.340
I did trust you and you got us lost, cheeseball.

01:32:52.340 --> 01:32:53.340
We're not lost.

01:32:53.340 --> 01:32:54.340
Watch it.

01:32:54.340 --> 01:32:56.660
Great, lame wad.

01:32:56.660 --> 01:32:58.660
Now we're lost and we can't read the map.

01:32:58.660 --> 01:33:00.660
You are such a loser.

01:33:00.660 --> 01:33:01.660
I'm not a loser.

01:33:01.660 --> 01:33:05.420
And we're not losers who came up on.

01:33:05.420 --> 01:33:08.420
We could circle back and take the red trail.

01:33:08.420 --> 01:33:10.420
Man, this is wax.

01:33:10.420 --> 01:33:12.420
Watch the edge.

01:33:12.420 --> 01:33:22.900
Grab my hand.

01:33:22.900 --> 01:33:38.520
Take the compass.

01:33:38.520 --> 01:33:46.060
Surely let you fall.

01:33:46.060 --> 01:33:48.060
The guys really were lost.

01:33:48.060 --> 01:33:50.060
It was just a pain at first,

01:33:50.060 --> 01:33:52.060
but nighttime was coming on fast

01:33:52.060 --> 01:33:54.060
and it was getting cold.

01:33:54.060 --> 01:34:04.730
It doesn't make sense.

01:34:04.730 --> 01:34:06.730
You even know how to use this?

01:34:06.730 --> 01:34:08.730
Give me a break.

01:34:08.730 --> 01:34:10.730
We've been going south for hours.

01:34:10.730 --> 01:34:12.730
We should have been in town by now.

01:34:12.730 --> 01:34:14.730
Look, the needle points north and we're heading south.

01:34:14.730 --> 01:34:16.730
What can I say?

01:34:16.730 --> 01:34:18.730
Is that the way you always hold it?

01:34:18.730 --> 01:34:19.730
Yeah, so?

01:34:19.730 --> 01:34:21.730
You're belt buckle genius.

01:34:21.730 --> 01:34:22.730
It's metal.

01:34:22.730 --> 01:34:25.730
The needle's always going to point to it because it's a magnet.

01:34:25.730 --> 01:34:26.730
Uh-oh.

01:34:26.730 --> 01:34:27.730
Yeah, uh-oh.

01:34:27.730 --> 01:34:29.730
We've been going the wrong way all day.

01:34:29.730 --> 01:34:31.730
Now we're lost and it's freezing.

01:34:31.730 --> 01:34:32.730
You are worthless.

01:34:32.730 --> 01:34:33.730
No, no.

01:34:33.730 --> 01:34:34.730
I know this place.

01:34:34.730 --> 01:34:37.730
We've got to be close to town.

01:34:37.730 --> 01:35:01.060
I should pound you.

01:35:01.060 --> 01:35:12.760
Maybe it's a ranger.

01:35:12.760 --> 01:35:14.760
Or maybe it's a hiker that knows his way back to town.

01:35:14.760 --> 01:35:15.760
I hope he's got a blanket.

01:35:15.760 --> 01:35:16.760
I'm freezing.

01:35:16.760 --> 01:35:17.760
Me too.

01:35:17.760 --> 01:35:18.760
Forget it.

01:35:18.760 --> 01:35:19.760
You can freeze.

01:35:19.760 --> 01:35:23.760
Maybe it's a maniac killing a hockey mask that's going to slash us.

01:35:23.760 --> 01:35:28.620
Or maybe you should stay here and let me do the talking.

01:35:28.620 --> 01:35:29.620
Uh, hey, hello?

01:35:29.620 --> 01:35:30.620
Who's there?

01:35:30.620 --> 01:35:32.620
Whoa, turn off the brights.

01:35:32.620 --> 01:35:35.890
Hello?

01:35:35.890 --> 01:35:37.890
What have we here?

01:35:37.890 --> 01:35:38.890
I'm Buzz.

01:35:38.890 --> 01:35:39.890
And this is Denny.

01:35:39.890 --> 01:35:42.890
We got lost and we can't find the trail back to town.

01:35:42.890 --> 01:35:43.890
Easy toad.

01:35:43.890 --> 01:35:45.890
You're not a ranger, are you?

01:35:45.890 --> 01:35:46.890
Ranger?

01:35:46.890 --> 01:35:47.890
No, not me.

01:35:47.890 --> 01:35:49.890
I'm traveling the same as you.

01:35:49.890 --> 01:35:51.890
Flynn's the name.

01:35:52.890 --> 01:35:54.890
So what are you doing up here?

01:35:54.890 --> 01:35:55.890
Are you lost too?

01:35:55.890 --> 01:35:57.890
Lost, me.

01:35:57.890 --> 01:36:00.890
Oh, you might say that.

01:36:00.890 --> 01:36:03.890
Oh, I suppose I couldn't be truly lost.

01:36:03.890 --> 01:36:05.890
I know these woods too well.

01:36:05.890 --> 01:36:06.890
We far from town?

01:36:06.890 --> 01:36:08.890
Farther than you know, my friends.

01:36:08.890 --> 01:36:09.890
Farther than you know.

01:36:09.890 --> 01:36:11.890
So can you help us get back?

01:36:11.890 --> 01:36:12.890
Me?

01:36:12.890 --> 01:36:13.890
Yeah, I do.

01:36:13.890 --> 01:36:15.890
I don't see anybody else here.

01:36:15.890 --> 01:36:17.890
You guys look half frozen.

01:36:17.890 --> 01:36:20.890
Tell you what, you follow me.

01:36:20.890 --> 01:36:25.450
And I'll lead you to someone who can help you.

01:36:25.450 --> 01:36:29.620
Wait.

01:36:29.620 --> 01:36:30.620
I wouldn't go with him.

01:36:30.620 --> 01:36:32.620
He gives me the creeps.

01:36:32.620 --> 01:36:34.620
You got a better idea?

01:36:34.620 --> 01:36:53.970
Don't worry, I can handle this too.

01:36:53.970 --> 01:36:55.970
Why don't you just tell us how to get back?

01:36:55.970 --> 01:36:56.970
Too far.

01:36:56.970 --> 01:36:58.970
You'll never find your way in the dark.

01:36:58.970 --> 01:37:00.970
So who's this guy you're taking us to?

01:37:00.970 --> 01:37:01.970
A good doctor.

01:37:01.970 --> 01:37:02.970
He's got a cottage.

01:37:02.970 --> 01:37:03.970
A little ways up here.

01:37:03.970 --> 01:37:04.970
In the woods?

01:37:04.970 --> 01:37:06.970
What kind of a doctor lives in the woods?

01:37:06.970 --> 01:37:07.970
Nations, boys.

01:37:07.970 --> 01:37:08.970
You'll see.

01:37:08.970 --> 01:37:11.970
By the way, how are you guys solving riddles?

01:37:11.970 --> 01:37:12.970
Riddles, why?

01:37:12.970 --> 01:37:13.970
Just asking.

01:37:13.970 --> 01:37:14.970
Just asking.

01:37:14.970 --> 01:37:21.420
There you go, boys.

01:37:21.420 --> 01:37:23.420
Home of the good doctor.

01:37:23.420 --> 01:37:26.420
Just like I promised.

01:37:26.420 --> 01:37:28.420
You guys thought I was joking, didn't you?

01:37:28.420 --> 01:37:34.490
Who lives here, the Seven Dwarfs?

01:37:34.490 --> 01:37:36.490
There's just one thing, guys.

01:37:36.490 --> 01:37:38.490
Before you go asking the doctor for help,

01:37:38.490 --> 01:37:40.490
you make sure you really need it.

01:37:40.490 --> 01:37:41.490
Why?

01:37:41.490 --> 01:37:45.490
Well, sometimes the price he charges is a little steep.

01:37:46.490 --> 01:37:50.490
So why don't you just tell us how...

01:37:50.490 --> 01:37:54.760
Yo, Flynn.

01:37:54.760 --> 01:37:55.760
This is creepy.

01:37:55.760 --> 01:37:56.760
Let's bolt.

01:37:56.760 --> 01:37:57.760
To where?

01:37:57.760 --> 01:38:01.540
We're lost, remember?

01:38:01.540 --> 01:38:02.540
We're not going in there.

01:38:02.540 --> 01:38:03.540
What else are we gonna do?

01:38:03.540 --> 01:38:05.540
It's freezing.

01:38:05.540 --> 01:38:07.540
Maybe he's got a phone.

01:38:07.540 --> 01:38:17.410
Gough, would ya?

01:38:17.410 --> 01:38:19.410
I'm sorry I got us lost, Danny.

01:38:19.410 --> 01:38:20.410
Don't worry.

01:38:20.410 --> 01:38:24.550
I'll smack you when we get home.

01:38:26.550 --> 01:38:28.550
What's that?

01:38:28.550 --> 01:38:30.550
Flynn, I know it's you.

01:38:30.550 --> 01:38:31.550
He's trying to scare us.

01:38:31.550 --> 01:38:35.020
He's doing a good job.

01:38:35.020 --> 01:38:36.020
Can't be him, too.

01:38:36.020 --> 01:38:38.020
Probably a raccoon.

01:38:38.020 --> 01:38:42.800
See, what's going on?

01:38:42.800 --> 01:38:57.130
You boys have made a very grave mistake.

01:38:57.130 --> 01:39:04.580
I don't suppose either of you are any good at riddles.

01:39:16.670 --> 01:39:27.760
Anybody here?

01:39:27.760 --> 01:39:29.760
Take a look at the new stuff on Nick.

01:39:29.760 --> 01:39:31.760
We got tunes, a place to snick.

01:39:31.760 --> 01:39:33.760
Plus the wildest games, animals, sports,

01:39:33.760 --> 01:39:36.760
brand new episodes, brand new shows, brand new...

01:39:42.400 --> 01:39:44.400
So don't be the last to find out.

01:39:44.400 --> 01:39:46.400
The First Kids Network's got great new stuff.

01:41:05.390 --> 01:41:10.310
And now to snick with Are You Afraid of the Dark?

01:41:10.310 --> 01:41:16.470
I think we have the wrong house, bye.

01:41:16.470 --> 01:41:19.470
Boys, boys, you've made a mistake.

01:41:19.470 --> 01:41:21.470
If you like my door at this time of night,

01:41:21.470 --> 01:41:24.470
you've taken a wrong turn and lost your way.

01:41:24.470 --> 01:41:25.470
Correct?

01:41:25.470 --> 01:41:26.470
Yeah.

01:41:26.470 --> 01:41:28.470
Happens all the time.

01:41:28.470 --> 01:41:30.470
Come in, come in, get warm.

01:41:30.470 --> 01:42:01.170
To Vink.

01:42:01.170 --> 01:42:02.170
Dr. Vink?

01:42:02.170 --> 01:42:05.170
Vink with a V, V, V, V, V.

01:42:05.170 --> 01:42:07.170
Who wants tea?

01:42:07.170 --> 01:42:09.170
I do.

01:42:09.170 --> 01:42:11.170
Hot tea on a cold night.

01:42:11.170 --> 01:42:13.170
Perfect.

01:42:13.170 --> 01:42:16.170
Flynn said you could help us find a way to get back to...

01:42:16.170 --> 01:42:18.170
Natural science.

01:42:18.170 --> 01:42:20.170
That's why I'm here, in case you're wondering.

01:42:20.170 --> 01:42:24.170
I've dedicated my life to studying flora and fauna.

01:42:24.170 --> 01:42:26.170
Who?

01:42:26.170 --> 01:42:28.170
There are many strange and wonderful things

01:42:28.170 --> 01:42:30.170
that occur in nature.

01:42:30.170 --> 01:42:34.170
But no one takes the time to really look and study.

01:42:34.170 --> 01:42:36.170
Observe.

01:42:36.170 --> 01:42:38.170
This guy's a nut bag.

01:42:38.170 --> 01:42:41.640
Behold.

01:42:41.640 --> 01:42:43.640
A true wonder of nature.

01:42:43.640 --> 01:42:46.640
The brain of a wild boar.

01:42:46.640 --> 01:42:53.580
I've discovered that long after the body dies,

01:42:53.580 --> 01:42:56.580
the brain still gives off electric impulses.

01:42:56.580 --> 01:43:02.730
Can you imagine if that energy could be harnessed?

01:43:02.730 --> 01:43:07.680
And I am not a nut bag.

01:43:07.680 --> 01:43:10.680
Look, my parents are probably going nuts by now.

01:43:10.680 --> 01:43:11.680
And, uh...

01:43:11.680 --> 01:43:12.680
Riddles.

01:43:12.680 --> 01:43:15.680
How are you boys at Riddles?

01:43:15.680 --> 01:43:17.680
Doc, we're tired and we just want to go home.

01:43:17.680 --> 01:43:19.680
Indeed, indeed.

01:43:19.680 --> 01:43:21.680
But first, the riddle.

01:43:21.680 --> 01:43:23.680
Try this one.

01:43:23.680 --> 01:43:26.680
How far can you walk into the woods?

01:43:26.680 --> 01:43:28.680
We don't want to do riddles.

01:43:28.680 --> 01:43:29.680
You must.

01:43:29.680 --> 01:43:31.680
Riddles exercise your brain.

01:43:31.680 --> 01:43:33.680
And where would you be with no brain?

01:43:33.680 --> 01:43:35.680
I don't know. Ask the wild boar.

01:43:35.680 --> 01:43:37.680
Halfway.

01:43:37.680 --> 01:43:38.680
Say what?

01:43:38.680 --> 01:43:40.680
He asked how far he can walk into the woods.

01:43:40.680 --> 01:43:41.680
Halfway.

01:43:41.680 --> 01:43:43.680
After that, you'll be walking out.

01:43:43.680 --> 01:43:45.680
Good! Very good!

01:43:45.680 --> 01:43:47.680
You may do.

01:43:47.680 --> 01:43:52.460
I'm going to call her, folks.

01:43:52.460 --> 01:43:54.460
No, no, not yet!

01:43:54.460 --> 01:43:56.460
We've only just begun.

01:43:56.460 --> 01:44:00.990
No, I think we're done.

01:44:00.990 --> 01:44:03.990
We play by my rules, or we don't play.

01:44:03.990 --> 01:44:05.990
What do you want?

01:44:05.990 --> 01:44:07.990
Another riddle?

01:44:07.990 --> 01:44:09.990
Here's the deal.

01:44:09.990 --> 01:44:11.990
I ask you a riddle,

01:44:11.990 --> 01:44:13.990
and if you solve it,

01:44:13.990 --> 01:44:15.990
you can call your parents.

01:44:15.990 --> 01:44:19.590
And if we don't solve it?

01:44:19.590 --> 01:44:22.940
Then you leave.

01:44:22.940 --> 01:44:24.940
That's it? We just leave?

01:44:24.940 --> 01:44:26.940
Simple, no?

01:44:26.940 --> 01:44:29.940
Let's do it. I'm good at riddles.

01:44:29.940 --> 01:44:37.220
Okay, what's the riddle?

01:44:37.220 --> 01:44:39.220
Wonderful! Wonderful!

01:44:41.550 --> 01:44:42.550
What riddle?

01:44:42.550 --> 01:44:45.960
Let's see. There's the...

01:44:45.960 --> 01:45:03.140
maybe the perfect choice.

01:45:03.140 --> 01:45:05.140
This is a riddle that has complexed many

01:45:05.140 --> 01:45:08.140
and confounded even more in our young lads.

01:45:08.140 --> 01:45:10.140
It's your turn to solve it.

01:45:10.140 --> 01:45:16.710
What is it?

01:45:16.710 --> 01:45:22.090
That has no weight and be seen by the naked eye.

01:45:22.090 --> 01:45:26.400
If you put it in a barrel,

01:45:26.400 --> 01:45:28.400
it would make the barrel lighter.

01:45:28.400 --> 01:45:33.860
I hate riddles.

01:45:33.860 --> 01:45:35.860
Okay, it's weightless.

01:45:35.860 --> 01:45:38.860
It can be seen by the naked eye,

01:45:38.860 --> 01:45:40.860
and if put in a barrel,

01:45:40.860 --> 01:45:43.860
it would make the barrel lighter.

01:45:43.860 --> 01:45:44.860
So?

01:45:44.860 --> 01:45:49.500
I don't know.

01:45:49.500 --> 01:45:54.280
Goodbye!

01:45:54.280 --> 01:45:56.280
I knew you wouldn't get it.

01:45:56.280 --> 01:46:00.420
What?

01:46:00.420 --> 01:46:02.420
You had your chance and failed.

01:46:03.420 --> 01:46:05.420
Like all the others.

01:46:05.420 --> 01:46:07.420
Others? What others?

01:46:07.420 --> 01:46:09.420
Go away.

01:46:09.420 --> 01:46:11.420
You know where the door is.

01:46:11.420 --> 01:46:13.420
But we're lost!

01:46:13.420 --> 01:46:15.420
Take a left on the trail,

01:46:15.420 --> 01:46:18.420
follow it to the dirt road and wait.

01:46:18.420 --> 01:46:20.420
A taxi cab will pick you up.

01:46:20.420 --> 01:46:22.420
A cab? In the woods?

01:46:22.420 --> 01:46:24.420
Comes by every night.

01:46:24.420 --> 01:46:27.420
Hurry. Or you'll miss it.

01:46:27.420 --> 01:46:36.020
Come on, dawg. Just let us use the phone.

01:46:36.020 --> 01:46:39.020
There is one way, I suppose.

01:46:39.020 --> 01:46:41.020
What? What's that?

01:46:41.020 --> 01:46:45.020
You can leave me a specimen.

01:46:45.020 --> 01:46:50.500
A specimen?

01:46:50.500 --> 01:46:54.500
You're much smarter than your brother gives you credit for.

01:46:54.500 --> 01:46:57.500
What kind of specimen?

01:46:57.500 --> 01:47:02.500
Something I can use in my experiments.

01:47:02.500 --> 01:47:06.500
Something valuable.

01:47:06.500 --> 01:47:08.500
Something fresh.

01:47:08.500 --> 01:47:26.730
Something like...

01:47:26.730 --> 01:47:28.730
Goodbye!

01:47:28.730 --> 01:47:30.730
For now.

01:47:30.730 --> 01:47:39.350
Wait a minute. No fair.

01:47:39.350 --> 01:47:43.350
You can't put a riddle in a story that can't be solved.

01:47:43.350 --> 01:47:45.350
Maybe it can.

01:47:45.350 --> 01:47:47.350
Yeah, right. It's weightless.

01:47:47.350 --> 01:47:51.350
You can see it, and if you put it in a barrel, it makes the barrel lighter.

01:47:51.350 --> 01:47:52.350
No way.

01:47:52.350 --> 01:47:55.350
Sounds like one of those riddles you can't solve.

01:47:55.350 --> 01:47:57.350
That's a cheat.

01:47:57.350 --> 01:48:00.350
No. Maybe it can be solved.

01:48:00.350 --> 01:48:04.350
Maybe you should all just lighten up and let me finish the story.

01:48:04.350 --> 01:48:10.380
Thank you.

01:48:10.380 --> 01:48:15.380
So, Denny and Buzz beat feet back into the woods.

01:48:15.380 --> 01:48:20.380
All they wanted was to get as far away from Dr. Vink as possible.

01:48:20.380 --> 01:48:26.120
Somebody's hand?

01:48:26.120 --> 01:48:28.120
You saw it. The guy's a lunatic.

01:48:28.120 --> 01:48:30.120
As soon as we get home, I'm calling the cops.

01:48:30.120 --> 01:48:34.230
We're still lost, you know?

01:48:34.230 --> 01:48:35.230
Yeah, I know.

01:48:35.230 --> 01:48:38.640
You don't think a cab's gonna come by?

01:48:38.640 --> 01:48:41.640
Yeah, real. There's no cabs in the woods.

01:48:41.640 --> 01:49:02.070
And are we ever glad you came by?

01:49:02.070 --> 01:49:13.220
Take us into town.

01:49:13.220 --> 01:49:15.220
Our pants will be the fur when we get home.

01:49:15.220 --> 01:49:19.980
Don't worry. I know you're good for it.

01:49:19.980 --> 01:49:20.980
Flynn!

01:49:20.980 --> 01:49:22.980
I figured I'd run into you guys again.

01:49:22.980 --> 01:49:24.980
I guess you didn't solve the riddle.

01:49:24.980 --> 01:49:26.980
How do you know? Who are you?

01:49:26.980 --> 01:49:30.980
I give a ride to folks who can't answer Dr. Vink's riddles.

01:49:30.980 --> 01:49:32.980
Happened to me around 40 years ago.

01:49:32.980 --> 01:49:38.120
Hold on. 40 years ago?

01:49:38.120 --> 01:49:41.120
I gave Dr. Vink a ride up here in my cab.

01:49:41.120 --> 01:49:44.120
He offered me a big tip if I could solve the riddle.

01:49:44.120 --> 01:49:47.120
I couldn't. So he took a specimen from me.

01:49:47.120 --> 01:49:49.120
What kind of specimen?

01:49:49.120 --> 01:49:50.120
He didn't see it at his house?

01:49:50.120 --> 01:49:53.120
Oh boy! I think it's one of his favorites.

01:49:53.120 --> 01:49:55.120
What is it? It's not what it is.

01:49:55.120 --> 01:49:57.120
It's what it was.

01:49:57.120 --> 01:50:01.430
Oh! He took your hand?

01:50:01.430 --> 01:50:03.430
I got off easy.

01:50:03.430 --> 01:50:06.430
40 years I've been bringing folks up to Dr. Vink's,

01:50:06.430 --> 01:50:08.430
hoping they can solve the riddle.

01:50:08.430 --> 01:50:11.430
But they don't. So they all end up here with me.

01:50:11.430 --> 01:50:12.430
What happens to them?

01:50:12.430 --> 01:50:14.430
Hey, Dr. Vink's needs his specimens.

01:50:14.430 --> 01:50:17.430
You're a lying sack. First of all, you're not that old.

01:50:17.430 --> 01:50:20.430
Didn't I tell you? Before the good doctor got his specimen,

01:50:20.430 --> 01:50:23.430
I had myself a nasty little accident.

01:50:23.430 --> 01:50:25.430
Crashed into this big old tree.

01:50:25.430 --> 01:50:27.430
You might say,

01:50:27.430 --> 01:50:29.430
I'm sort of dying!

01:50:29.430 --> 01:50:39.790
They all died. Just like me.

01:50:39.790 --> 01:50:42.790
Every night I had the same accident with a different fare.

01:50:42.790 --> 01:50:44.790
It's kind of a curse.

01:50:44.790 --> 01:50:48.790
You've probably heard some of my fares up around Dr. Vink's house.

01:50:48.790 --> 01:50:50.790
The bushes! They were ghosts!

01:50:50.790 --> 01:50:54.790
Nobody can leave until someone solves Dr. Vink's riddle.

01:50:54.790 --> 01:50:56.790
I was hoping the two of you could do it.

01:50:56.790 --> 01:50:58.790
You know, somehow break the spell.

01:50:58.790 --> 01:51:01.790
Oh well. Wait till you see the accident we're going to have.

01:51:01.790 --> 01:51:03.790
It's going to be a real doozy.

01:51:03.790 --> 01:51:06.790
This is your fault! You said you could solve the riddle.

01:51:06.790 --> 01:51:10.790
Still got time. You don't crash another old 30 seconds.

01:51:10.790 --> 01:51:12.790
I think that's boys.

01:51:12.790 --> 01:51:13.790
Think!

01:51:13.790 --> 01:51:15.790
Okay, okay. It's weightless.

01:51:15.790 --> 01:51:17.790
It could be seen by the naked eye.

01:51:17.790 --> 01:51:19.790
And it's put in a barrel.

01:51:19.790 --> 01:51:26.050
It'll make the barrel lighter.

01:51:26.050 --> 01:51:29.050
We're dead. We're dead!

01:51:29.050 --> 01:51:34.050
I can't think like this!

01:51:34.050 --> 01:51:36.050
You have to.

01:51:36.050 --> 01:51:39.050
It's helium. Helium will make the barrel lighter.

01:51:39.050 --> 01:51:41.050
But you can't see helium!

01:51:41.050 --> 01:51:43.050
Won't be long now.

01:51:43.050 --> 01:51:45.050
What can you see that's weightless?

01:51:45.050 --> 01:51:48.050
Air. But you can't see air.

01:51:48.050 --> 01:51:50.050
Or can you?

01:51:50.050 --> 01:51:53.050
Wait a second. There's a trick here.

01:51:53.050 --> 01:51:56.050
You can't put something in the barrel to make it lighter.

01:51:56.050 --> 01:51:58.050
You have to take something out.

01:51:58.050 --> 01:52:02.870
If you take something out of the barrel itself, it'll be lighter.

01:52:02.870 --> 01:52:04.870
Wait till you see the explosion we're going to make.

01:52:04.870 --> 01:52:06.870
I got it! I know the answer!

01:52:06.870 --> 01:52:07.870
Where is it?

01:52:07.870 --> 01:52:09.870
It's weightless. You can see it.

01:52:09.870 --> 01:52:31.870
And if you put it in the barrel, it'll make the barrel...

01:52:31.870 --> 01:52:32.870
Live!

01:52:32.870 --> 01:52:33.870
Where's the cab?

01:52:33.870 --> 01:52:35.870
It's gone.

01:52:35.870 --> 01:52:37.870
Where's the curse? We're saved!

01:52:37.870 --> 01:52:44.260
We didn't break the curse.

01:52:44.260 --> 01:52:46.260
You did.

01:52:46.260 --> 01:52:48.260
Nice going.

01:52:48.260 --> 01:52:58.190
But you're still a loser.

01:52:58.190 --> 01:52:59.190
Not again!

01:52:59.190 --> 01:53:05.830
You're Denny and Buzz Crocker?

01:53:05.830 --> 01:53:07.830
Yeah.

01:53:07.830 --> 01:53:10.830
Your parents have been going nuts looking for you.

01:53:10.830 --> 01:53:12.830
The whole town's in an uproar.

01:53:12.830 --> 01:53:14.830
Come on, Gideon.

01:53:14.830 --> 01:53:23.230
What are you boys doing here anyway?

01:53:23.230 --> 01:53:25.230
Tell me something.

01:53:25.230 --> 01:53:27.230
How are you at riddles?

01:53:27.230 --> 01:53:30.230
No one ever saw the phantom cab again.

01:53:30.230 --> 01:53:35.230
And when the boys brought the police back to Dr. Wink's cottage,

01:53:35.230 --> 01:53:40.230
all that was left was an old stone foundation

01:53:40.230 --> 01:53:43.480
covered with weeds.

01:53:43.480 --> 01:53:50.270
The end.

01:53:50.270 --> 01:53:52.270
And now the vote.

01:53:52.270 --> 01:53:55.270
Thumbs up means Frank's in, thumbs down he's not.

01:53:55.270 --> 01:53:57.270
And it has to be anonymous.

01:53:57.270 --> 01:54:05.100
David, Kiki,

01:54:05.100 --> 01:54:08.500
Diane,

01:54:08.500 --> 01:54:10.500
Kristen,

01:54:10.500 --> 01:54:11.500
Eric,

01:54:14.740 --> 01:54:16.740
and me.

01:54:16.740 --> 01:54:18.740
Congratulations, Frank.

01:54:18.740 --> 01:54:20.740
Welcome to the Midnight Society.

01:54:20.740 --> 01:54:21.740
Good job.

01:54:21.740 --> 01:54:25.900
Denny.

01:54:25.900 --> 01:54:26.900
Frank.

01:54:26.900 --> 01:55:18.270
We snicked.

01:55:18.270 --> 01:55:19.270
They will have snicked.

01:55:19.270 --> 01:55:21.270
It is post-snick.

01:55:21.270 --> 01:55:24.270
You can sneak again next Saturday night on Nickelodeon.

